# EA Assistant — Local Project Context

Copy this file to `ea-assistant.local.md` in your project root and fill in the fields above.
Claude will load this context automatically when you use `/ea-open`.

## Configuration Fields

- **engagement_name** — The name of the EA engagement (used in artifact headers and reports)
- **organization** — Client or organisation name
- **architect_name** — Lead architect's name (appears in artifact footers)
- **architecture_scope** — Brief description of what domains/systems are in scope
- **start_date** — Engagement start date (YYYY-MM format)
- **current_phase** — Active ADM phase (Prelim, Req, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, or H)
- **completed_phases** — List of phases already completed, e.g. `["Prelim", "Req"]`
- **requirements_repo_path** — Optional path to an external requirements file or repo to sync from
